		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I ask this because I am making a &quot;NES to jamma&quot; pcb.   With the release of the &quot;NES RGB&quot; ppu replacement, I can now feed rgb to an arcade monitor.  I plan on mounting the NES controller socket to my adapter so the gun will plug and play... But I didn't know if I need to add 2 sockets for 2 guns.  It sounds like it may not be worth adding a second socket with only a few games using 2 guns.....  I didn't realize you could control the duck in duck hunt.<br /><br />Any other games out there?<br /><br />I'm in the final stages of my schematic.   Thanks for any and all input!<br /><br />Mark

		

